items.traditional_solution:
The expression is

$$
\frac{5+5+5}{7+7+7} - \frac{5+5+5}{7+7+7} + \frac{5}{7}
$$

Notice that the first two terms are identical. In mathematics, any value subtracted from itself results in zero.

Therefore,

$$
\left( \frac{5+5+5}{7+7+7} - \frac{5+5+5}{7+7+7} \right) + \frac{5}{7}
=
0 + \frac{5}{7}
=
\frac{5}{7}
$$

